Hey Everyone,

My names Jonathon Vincent, I have reciently completed Computer 
Science at RMIT University in Melbourne. In my final Semester I 
worked on a research project which combined NEAT with an agent 
modelling system Repast. I also attempted cooperative coevolution 
with a team of three predators attempting to catch a prey.

If your interested in what I've done you can check out my paper:

http://yallara.cs.rmit.edu.au/~jovincen/report2003.pdf

(I'm hoping that compy doesnt have any spelling mistakes :)

I combined Ugo's JNEAT code with Repast. My system isn't exactly 
user friendly at the moment. There is a lot I'd like to fix. I could 
put something up if people were really really really interested :P

Although I do keep putting it off (I'm teaching myself Vis 
Studio .NET atm ... i know its the dark side but I gotta eat :P)

My interest in NEAT at the moment however is purely for fun. I am 
considering honours next year but I dont think this will be the 
case. (I shudder at one more year of school).

I would like to continue my experiements to see if indeed I can find 
a solution to my problem. I didnt have enough time in my research 
project :S

Also, I would like one of those shiny new apple's (fastest desktop 
computer or something like that).. Normally I avoid apples but my 
experiements take weeks to get anywhere.. :D

feel free to contact me should you have any questions. I'll see what 
I can do.

cheers,
Jono

p.s. Has anyone considered a Non-Yahoo (ie, no annoying adds) forum 
for our little club?
